<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Class to conveniently track Seeds within SeedBundles. Saves newly collected</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><Highlight kind="comment">/// seeds in the proper bundle. Supports constant-time removal, as seeds and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><Highlight kind="comment">/// entire bundles are vectorized and marked used to signify removal. Iterators</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><Highlight kind="comment">/// skip bundles that are completely used.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/seedcontainer"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sandboxir/seedcontainer/#a8e0dc6e42ef6fab7dfe651f2610b87fb">SeedContainer</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Use the same key for different seeds if they are the same type and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// reference the same pointer, even if at different offsets. This directs</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// potentially vectorizable seeds into the same bundle.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">using </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">KeyT = std::tuple&lt;Value &#42;, Type &#42;, Instruction::Opcode&gt;;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Trying to vectorize too many seeds at once is expensive in</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00180" /><CodeLine lineNumber="180"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// compilation-time. Use a vector of bundles (all with the same key) to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00181" /><CodeLine lineNumber="181"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// partition the candidate set into more manageable units. Each bundle is</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// size-limited by sbvec-seed-bundle-size-limit.  TODO: There might be a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="183"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// better way to divide these than by simple insertion order.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="184"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">using </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">ValT = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;std::unique&#95;ptr&lt;SeedBundle&gt;</a>&gt;;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// Iterates over the \\p Map of SeedBundle Vectors, starting at \\p MapIt,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// and \\p Vec at \\p VecIdx, skipping vectors that are completely</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// used. Iteration order over the keys &#123;Pointer, Type, Opcode&#125; follows</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// DenseMap iteration order. For a given key, the vectors of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// SeedBundles will be returned in insertion order. As in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// pseudo code below:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// for Key,Value in Bundles</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///   for SeedBundleVector in Value</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///     for SeedBundle in SeedBundleVector</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///        if !SeedBundle.allUsed() ...</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="222"><Highlight kind="comment">    ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="223"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// Note that the bundles themselves may have additional ordering, created</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="224"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// by the subclasses by insertAt. The bundles themselves may also have used</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="225"><Highlight kind="comment">    /// instructions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// TODO: Range&#95;size counts fully used-bundles. Further, iterating over</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
